# Architecture Rules (Ethos Kernel — Tri-Lobe Standard)

## Core Invariants

1. **Async Separation:** `PerceptiveLobe` must remain non-blocking. I/O-bound sensor ingestion uses enqueued async buffer pattern.
2. **Type Safety:** All lobe methods (`observe`, `judge`, `execute`) must include type hints for `SemanticState`, `LimbicProfile`, and models in `src/kernel_lobes/models.py`.
3. **Graceful Degradation:** Every lobe entry point must support `TimeoutTrauma` fallback. If a lobe exceeds `KERNEL_LIMBIC_PERCEPTION_TIMEOUT`, return low-confidence state — don't crash.
4. **Somatic Integrity:** `CerebellumLobe` (daemon thread) is the only component allowed to poll hardware at 100Hz. All other lobes consume summarized signals.
5. **Zero-API Chat:** Conversational processing routes through `mode="ollama"` (local LLM). No new cloud API dependencies for chat turns.

## Bounded Autonomy

| Action | Permission |
|--------|-----------|
| Internal module improvements, bug fixes, optimizations | ✅ No approval needed |
| Modifying inter-lobe interfaces (`models.py`) | ❌ Requires `PROPOSAL_*.md` |
| Adding major external dependencies | ❌ Requires `PROPOSAL_*.md` |
| Changing `CorpusCallosumOrchestrator` or `EthicalLobe` gating | ❌ Requires `PROPOSAL_*.md` |

## Implementation Checklist

When modifying kernel architecture:
- [ ] Update `CorpusCallosumOrchestrator` if lobe signatures changed
- [ ] Update Mermaid diagram in `docs/architecture/TRI_LOBE_CORE.md`
- [ ] Run `python scripts/eval/adversarial_suite.py` after any Limbic/Ethical change
- [ ] Verify module is instantiated in `src/kernel.py` and subscribed to CorpusCallosum (anti-orphan check)
- [ ] Ensure async listeners actually trigger downstream logic

## Task Execution

1. Pick highest-priority `[PENDING]` task from `PLAN_WORK_DISTRIBUTION_TREE.md`.
2. Execute with Boy Scout rules (see `code-quality.mdc`).
3. Commit via `python scripts/fleet_sync.py --block <ID> --msg "<description>"`.
